United States International University Africa has called for soccer trials for sports scholarship on March 25-26, at the varsity grounds. The two-day event will be conducted from 9 am-5 pm. Those willing to be part of the soccer team must have met the minimum university entry points. The athletes will also be required to carry their original certificates as well as organise personal transport and accommodation. Other sports disciplines that offer sports scholarship includes hockey and rugby. The university is accredited by the Commission for Higher Education (CUE) in Kenya and by the Western Association of Schools and Colleges (WASC) in the United States. The university campus is located in the Roysambu neighbourhood, in the Kasarani suburb of Nairobi, Kenya's capital and largest city Over 130 nationalities are represented among the student population undertaking 24 undergraduate, graduate and doctoral programs at USIU Africa.